    ├── screenshots/
    │   ├── Inventory_Analytics.png
    │   └── Delivery_Performance.png
    └── README.md
nventory Turnover Calculation Approach

Inventory turnover measures how efficiently inventory is utilized over time.

Formula Used:
Inventory Turnover Ratio (Value)
Inventory Turnover = Total Sales / Average Inventory Value
Inventory Turnover Ratio (Units)
Inventory Turnover (Units) = Units Sold / Average Stock Quantity
DAX Measures:
Total Sales = SUM(Fact_table[sales])
Units Sold = SUM(Fact_table[order_item_quantity])
Avg Inventory Value = AVERAGE(Fact_table[inventory_value])
Purpose:
Higher turnover → Efficient inventory management
Lower turnover → Overstocking or low demand
Slow-Moving & Fast-Moving Inventory Identification Logic
Logic Used:
Fast-Moving Inventory
High inventory turnover ratio
High sales volume
Slow-Moving Inventory
Low inventory turnover ratio
Low sales volume
Classification Approach:

Products are ranked using:

Turnover Rank = RANKX(
    ALL(Fact_table[category_name]),
    [Inventory Turnover Ratio],
    ,
    DESC
)
Categories:
Top-ranked items → Fast-moving
Bottom-ranked items → Slow-moving
Business Importance:
Helps reduce holding costs
Identifies dead stock
Improves demand planning
Delivery Performance Analysis Methodology
Key Metrics Used:
Delivery Delay = Actual Delivery Date – Scheduled Delivery Date

On-Time Delivery Rate

On-Time Delivery % = 
(Number of On-Time Deliveries / Total Deliveries) * 100
Analysis Approach:
Compare scheduled vs actual delivery dates
Identify delayed shipments
Analyze performance by region, shipping mode, and category
Insights Derived:
Delay patterns across regions
Inefficient shipping methods
Impact of delays on customer satisfaction
📈 Key Insights
Certain product categories show high turnover, indicating strong demand.
Some categories are slow-moving, leading to excess inventory and higher storage costs.
Delivery delays are concentrated in specific regions and shipping modes.
On-time delivery performance varies significantly across categories.
Conclusion

This dashboard enhances supply chain visibility by providing actionable insights into inventory and delivery performance. It enables businesses to make data-driven decisions, reduce costs, and improve operational efficiency.
